BULLETIN
Tropical Depression Eugene Advisory Number  20
NWS National Hurricane Center Miami FL       EP052017
800 AM PDT Wed Jul 12 2017

...EUGENE WEAKENS TO A TROPICAL DEPRESSION...


SUMMARY OF 800 AM PDT...1500 UTC...INFORMATION
----------------------------------------------
LOCATION...23.6N 121.8W
ABOUT 510 MI...815 KM WSW OF PUNTA EUGENIA MEXICO
MAXIMUM SUSTAINED WINDS...35 MPH...55 KM/H
PRESENT MOVEMENT...NW OR 320 DEGREES AT 10 MPH...17 KM/H
MINIMUM CENTRAL PRESSURE...1006 MB...29.71 INCHES


WATCHES AND WARNINGS
--------------------
There are no coastal watches or warnings in effect.


DISCUSSION AND 48-HOUR OUTLOOK
------------------------------
At 800 AM PDT (1500 UTC), the center of Tropical Depression Eugene
was located near latitude 23.6 North, longitude 121.8 West. The
depression is moving toward the northwest near 10 mph (17 km/h) and
this motion is expected to continue for the next couple of days.

Maximum sustained winds are near 35 mph (55 km/h) with higher gusts.
Some weakening is forecast during the next 48 hours and Eugene is
expected to become a remnant low by tonight.

The estimated minimum central pressure is 1006 mb (29.71 inches).


HAZARDS AFFECTING LAND
----------------------
SURF:  Swells generated by Eugene are affecting portions of the west
coast of northern Baja California peninsula and southern California.
These swells are likely to cause life-threatening surf and rip
current conditions.  Please consult products from your local weather
office.


NEXT ADVISORY
-------------
Next complete advisory at 200 PM PDT.

$$
Forecaster Landsea

NNNN
